  <description><![CDATA[<p>In a quiet location surrounded by a large garden and century-old trees, the family-run Hotel Masson looks out over the deep blue waters of Lake Geneva. If you love history and culture, then this is the hotel for you - it's the oldest hotel in the area and a member of Swiss Historic Hotels. The picturesque <span>Château de Chillon</span> is nearby and you'll get one free entrance per person per stay.</p>
<p>The sights and sounds of Montreux's bustling centre are a pleasant stroll along the lakeside path - it's a musical city famous for the Montreux Jazz Festival in July, and being the recording location for many of Queen's albums - look out for the huge Freddie Mercury statue on the edge of the lake.</p>
<h2>Lake views and romantic design</h2>
<p>This elegant Belle Epoque-style hotel dates back to 1829 and is in a peaceful spot between the lake and mountains so there's a variety of walking trails nearby. Make sure you're back at the hotel for sunset - the garden gets an incredible view.</p>
<p>Rooms are individually decorated - the romantic design is a reminder of times gone by, whilst modern facilities (and the cosiest of beds) make for an exceedingly comfortable stay. Enjoy a warm welcome, exceptional hospitality, and delicious meals. The hotel uses local produce so make sure you try the freshly-baked bread and homemade jam made from home-grown fruits.</p>]]></description>
